			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><b><a href="http://www.mikeresnick.com">By Mike Resnick.</a></b><br />
Read by Paul Fischer (of <a href="http://www.balticonpodcast.org">The Balticon Podcast</a>)</p>

<p><i>&#8220;Very good, Barnaby,&#8221; she says. &#8220;And what is this?&#8221;</i></p>

<p><i>&#8220;Kitten,&#8221; I say.</i> </p>

<p><i>We go through the whole book.</i></p>

<p><i>&#8220;Where is Barnaby?&#8221; I ask.</i></p>

<p><i>&#8220;Barnaby is an ape,&#8221; she says. &#8220;There is no picture of an ape in the book.&#8221;</i></p>

<p><i>I wonder if there are any other Barnabys in the world, and if they are lonely too.</i></p>

<p><b>Rated G</b>.  Contains nothing age-inappropriate.  However, some listeners may find it excessively sad.</p>

