<p><i>After ascending 72 flights of iron stairs, creeping past tentacled sentinels lurking in pools filled with black water, and silently dispatching wizened old warriors armed with glaives and morningstars that proved a close match for his pistols and poisoned glass knives, Mr. Zealand at last stumbled into the uppermost room of Archibald Grace&#8217;s invisible tower. All Zealand&#8217;s earlier murders were mere journeyman work compared to this final assassination, the murder of a man who&#8217;d lived for untold centuries, who&#8217;d come to America and enslaved Buffalo spirits, who&#8217;d built this tower of ice and iron on the far side of the Rockies as a sanctuary and stronghold for his own precious life.</i></p>

